
[1]rigidly

   RIG'IDLY, adv.

   1. Stuffy; unpliantly.

   2. Severely; strictly; exactly; without laxity, indulgence or
   abatement; as, to judge rigidly; to criticize rigidly; to execute a law
   rigidly.
